cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with domain adaptation in visual datasets using a novel CNN architecture. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new approach to automatically discover latent domains, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves the use of novel layers to align the distribution of CNN internal feature representations, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which could place it under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves the use of publicly-available datasets, which could place it under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
